section.section:
The following offenses, committed in violation of this title or of any regulation adopted under this title, are grounds for revocation of a license to catch oysters under this section:
Taking oysters located more than 200 feet within a closed or prohibited area;
Taking oysters with gear that is prohibited in that area;
Taking oysters outside of a time restriction for the harvest of oysters by more than 1 hour;
Taking oysters during closed seasons; and
Taking oysters from a leased area by a person other than the leaseholder or the leaseholder's designee.
